<p itemprop="description">A lead solution architect uses their expert knowledge and experience to direct work addressing high level and complex solution scenarios. They support and lead other solution architects, set strategic direction, and champion solution architecture across the organisation.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and direct the application of solution architectural principles, methods, and tools across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish solution architecture strategy and standards across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide expert consultancy on complex solution transformation challenges</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cross-organisational initiatives and major solution architecture programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop the solution architecture capability and community</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with senior leadership to align solution architecture with organisational strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion solution architecture best practices and maturity across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in external solution architecture communities and forums</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive digital transformation through innovative solution delivery</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisation-wide platform and integration strategies</li>
    </ul>
</section>

